					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><p class="mw-empty-elt">

</p>
<figure class="mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Monasterio_viejo_de_San_Juan_de_la_Penna.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Monasterio_viejo_de_San_Juan_de_la_Penna.jpg/300px-Monasterio_viejo_de_San_Juan_de_la_Penna.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="400" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Monasterio_viejo_de_San_Juan_de_la_Penna.jpg/450px-Monasterio_viejo_de_San_Juan_de_la_Penna.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Monasterio_viejo_de_San_Juan_de_la_Penna.jpg/600px-Monasterio_viejo_de_San_Juan_de_la_Penna.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1200" data-file-height="1600" /></a><figcaption>The <a href="/wiki/Way_of_St._James" class="mw-redirect" title="Way of St. James">Way of St. James</a> (el Camino de Santiago), is the pilgrimage to the <a href="/wiki/Cathedral_of_Santiago_de_Compostela" class="mw-redirect" title="Cathedral of Santiago de Compostela">Cathedral of Santiago de Compostela</a> where legend has it that it holds the remains of the apostle, <a href="/wiki/Saint_James_the_Great" class="mw-redirect" title="Saint James the Great">Saint James the Great</a>. The route was declared  the first <a href="/wiki/European_Cultural_Route" class="mw-redirect" title="European Cultural Route">European Cultural Route</a> by the <a href="/wiki/Council_of_Europe" title="Council of Europe">Council of Europe</a> in October 1987; it was also named one of <a href="/wiki/List_of_World_Heritage_Sites_in_Spain" title="List of World Heritage Sites in Spain">UNESCO's World Heritage Sites</a> in 1993.</figcaption></figure>
